From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andreas Rehn <rehn.andreas86@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 21 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] riscv: Add Milk-V Duo S (CV1813H/SG2000) board support

Add support for the Milk-V Duo S development board based on the
Sophgo SG2000 (CV1813H) SoC. This SoC is pin-compatible with the
CV1800B and shares the same peripheral IP blocks, so we reuse the
existing cv1800b cpu and driver code.

Changes:
- Add board/sophgo/milkv_duo_s/ with Kconfig for TARGET_MILKV_DUO_S
- Add arch/riscv/dts/cv1813h-milkv-duo-s.dts and cv1813h.dtsi
- Add configs/milkv_duo_s_defconfig
- Register milkv_duo_s in arch/riscv/cpu/cv1800b Kconfig
- Add DTS build entry in arch/riscv/dts/Makefile

The SG2000 has 512MB DDR vs 64MB on CV1800B, and uses SDHCI0 for
the SD card slot.

Upstream-Status: Pending

Signed-off-by: Andreas Rehn <rehn.andreas86@gmail.com>
